value.metadata:
{"function": "available_maf = 0

months = [2,3,4,5,6]
if date.month in months:
    
    runoff_maf_95 = self.GET("node/77821/1529", **kwargs)
    
    # calculate water bank deficit - the assumption is that Cherry is used to fill WB deficit
    #WB_taf = self.GET("network/1134/1322", offset=-1, **kwargs)
    #WB_max_taf = self.GET("network/1134/1528", **kwargs)
    #WB_deficit_maf = max(WB_max_taf - WB_taf, 0) / 1000 # deficit
    WB_deficit_maf = 10
    
    # get reservoir storage in MAF
    HH_storage = self.GET("node/77822/68", offset=-1, **kwargs)
    HH_storage_maf = HH_storage / 1000
    
    HH_max_storage = self.GET("node/77822/63", **kwargs)
    HH_max_storage_maf = HH_max_storage / 1000
    HH_storage_deficit_maf = HH_max_storage_maf - HH_storage_maf
    
    # get estimated year-to-go delivery in MAF
    # delivery_maf = 0   # not used for holm
    
    # get estimated year-to-go environmental release in MAF
    instream_maf = 0
    
    # estimate probability of filling
    #if CE_storage_maf + runoff_maf_95 - WB_deficit_maf - instream_maf >= 0:
    
    available_maf = max(runoff_maf_95 - HH_storage_deficit_maf - instream_maf, 0)

return available_maf", "modified_date": "2019-02-02 20:04:26", "modified_by": "3", "use_function": "Y", "note": "", "source": "OpenAgua/david@openagua.org", "user_id": "2", "cr_date": "2019-02-01 10:12:47"}

This is the total snow stored in a basin.
An arbitrarily defined variable to describe future runoff.
Flow requirements in the region depend on water year types. Water Year Type tracks this, and can be a scalar or descriptor time series.
